From d744ad36740ac5e593d5e537ea30759c431da4e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 05:27:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] libv4l2: Prevent infinite loop when fopen fails due to
 SELinux denial

If SELinux or filesystem permissions deny access to a sysfs video node,
the while loop in `get_video_nodes()` gets stuck continuously trying to
open the exact same node index indefinitely, causing the entire
`cameraserver` and camera application to freeze.

This commit fixes the bug by properly incrementing the node index (`i++`)
and continuing to the next node when `fopen` fails.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 libv4l2/exynos_v4l2.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/libv4l2/exynos_v4l2.c b/libv4l2/exynos_v4l2.c
index cc838c2..4d1760c 100644
--- a/libv4l2/exynos_v4l2.c
+++ b/libv4l2/exynos_v4l2.c
@@ -136,6 +136,7 @@ int exynos_v4l2_open_devname(const char *devname, int oflag, ...)
             stream_fd = fopen(filename, "r");
             if (stream_fd == NULL) {
                 ALOGE("failed to open sysfs entry for videodev");
+                i++;
                 continue;   /* try next */
             }
 
